        "title": "feat(scaleway): add direct SSH lease provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add Scaleway as a direct Linux SSH-lease provider using the official SDK\n- implement acquire, resolve, touch, release, cleanup, doctor, claim recovery, per-lease IAM SSH keys, ownership tags, and all-pages inventory\n- propagate command contexts into every SDK request and use bounded rollback cleanup\n- redact both environment and SDK-profile credentials from SDK validation errors\n- preserve ambiguous-create access while safely reconciling proven key-only rollback claims\n- add provider docs, generated metadata, and guarded live-smoke coverage\n\nReplaces https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/pull/432 because its contributor branch could not be updated with the current `main` workflow changes using the available OAuth scope.\n\nCloses https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/366\n\nCo-authored-by: @coygeek\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test ./internal/providers/scaleway ./internal/providers/all ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `go test -race ./...` (all provider packages passed; three unrelated macOS permission tests also fail on clean `main`)\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `node --test scripts/live-scaleway-smoke.test.js`\n- `node scripts/check-provider-matrix.mjs`\n- `bash scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `go test -race ./internal/providers/scaleway ./internal/providers/all`\n- Codex autoreview of the full provider branch and the live deletion fix at `355633fe`; no accepted or actionable findings\n\n## Live proof\n\n- created a dedicated application credential limited to `InstancesFullAccess` and `SSHKeysFullAccess`\n- doctor reported authentication ready and the initial owned inventory was empty\n- provisioned a DEV1-S instance in `fr-par-1`, waited for ready, executed an SSH command, and confirmed owned inventory visibility\n- the first run exposed Scaleway's requirement to power off a running server before deletion; release and rollback now power off, wait for stopped state, and delete, with fake-API regression coverage\n- reran the full guarded smoke successfully through create, status, SSH, stop, cleanup dry-run, and final empty inventory (`[]`)\n- cleanup completed with no live resources left; the credential is stored in 1Password and was not placed in repository config or command arguments\n\n## Security and configuration\n\nScaleway API credentials remain in SDK config or environment only. Repository configuration contains non-secret project, region, zone, image, type, and optional existing security-group identifiers.\n",
